transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the on Print shop.
In this video we'll take you on a tour of the exciting new upgrades we've rolled out for the front stores in this release.
In version 12.0, several exciting features were introduced to enhance the user experience and streamline operations.

These include the Buy Now feature for instant purchases, the ability to create product option wise shipping packages, and the grouping of shipments for same size products to simplify packaging and delivery.
The Buy Now feature is particularly useful for ready to buy print products with minimal or no customization.
To enable this functionality, admins can navigate to the Ready to Buy Products menu, select a product and enable the Buy Now setting under Configuration Details.
Once activated, a Buy Now button appears on the storefront alongside the Continue Checkout button, allowing users to proceed directly to the shopping cart for a quick and seamless purchase.
Another significant enhancement is the ability to create fixed shipping packages for product options, which is ideal for packaging additional hardware components alongside the main product.
For example, if a banner is the main product and a banner stand is an optional add on, admins can create a product option such as Do you need a stand with attributes like Yes and No?
The yes attribute can be assigned a specific weight which is considered during package creation.
Using the New Product Options tab in the Package Configuration section, admins can define fixed shipping packages either option wise or product specific option wise.
Once set up, the Shipping Summary will display these packages automatically, including them in the shipping details.

The grouping of shipments is another valuable functionality introduced in this version, allowing products of the same size to be consolidated into a single package, thereby simplifying logistics and reducing shipping costs.

To enable this feature, admins must activate the Group Shipment setting in Site Settings, configure the Shipping Price Calculator or Split call setting to order product wise and ensure that shipping packages are created for the products.
Once enabled, the system merges same size products into a single shipment which can be verified on the Shipping summary screen.
These updates in version 12.0 enhanced efficiency and provide a seamless experience for both admins and customers.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
